SIMPLE: flying_squirrel
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Flying squirrel
<hw>Fly"ing squir"rel</hw> <pr>(? or ?)</pr>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>One of a group of squirrels, of the genus <gen>Glaucomys</gen>
(formerly <gen>Pteromus</gen> and <gen>Sciuropterus</gen> [1913
Webster]), especially <spn>Glaucomys volans</spn> and <spn>Glaucomys
sabrinus</spn>, having parachute-like folds of skin extending from the
fore to the hind legs, which enable them to make very long, gliding
leaps.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The species of Pteromys are large, with bushy tails, and
inhabit southern Asia and the East Indies; those of Sciuropterus are
smaller, with flat tails, and inhabit the northern parts of Europe,
Asia, and America. The American species <spn>(Sciuropterus
volucella)</spn> is also called Assapan. The Australian flying
squirrels, or flying phalangers, are marsupials. See <cref>Flying
phalanger</cref> (above).</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>flyleaf</ent>⟦br⟧
